16th Rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usharpiemharkur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharpie Mharkur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 9:58:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22641.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Family  VS  EQ</span><hr size=1> to Crrow's post:  I was like that until I realized my friend wasn't ever going to stop playing and if I wanted to stay a part of her life I needed to start playing too...  Now I play a little more than she does...  ;p  But to be honest if she's not playing, I don't much feel like either...  I think it's more a question of how much someone really cares about you being happy, and I mean that for both those playing and those not...  I would suggest though to at least take a one week break every month or two, just to make sure you can still do it...  If not, you should probably start listening to your folks... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usharpiemharkur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharpie Mharkur</A> at: 3/6/02 9:59:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umuuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 10:02:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22641.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Family  VS  EQ</span><hr size=1> Just a couple observations... playing EQ in moderation is perfectly harmless and good fun.  After all, would &lt;insert family member here&gt; prefer I be out in a bar drinking myself silly?<br>
<br>
That said, RL should come first.  EQ should not encroach upon family/friend interaction.  Obviously everyone needs some relaxation time and EQ is a perfectly reasonable way to spend that time.  But skipping play time with your kid to go on a Kael raid isn't exactly cool.<br>
<br>
Muuk<br>
49 rogue<br>
Zeb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usekoye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sekoye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 12:18:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22641.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> I have been playing this game since the start.  I used to live on my own, and EQ was a great escape.  I recently moved back home to help out since my mom had a stroke, then low and behold my lung had collapsed, so it all worked out for the best that I had moved home.  I am one of those people that play, and when I play I play hard.  <br>
<br>
I am a member of a top guild on my server, and there isn't much we haven't done.  Just this past year I have started to realize that EQ is more fun when taken in moderation.  For instance, set one day off a week to just spend with your family.  One day to spend with friends.  One day for TV. And so on.   For myself:<br>
<br>
Monday: Cleaning day<br>
Tuesday: Friends<br>
Wednesday: Guild, Guild raids<br>
Thursday: TV day<br>
Friday: Guild, Guild Raids<br>
Saturday: Mourning from 9am to 4pm guild, evening to 4-5am is friends.<br>
Sunday:  Just family.<br>
<br>
Since I've started doing this for the past year, I have not only noticed that my attitude in game as well as with family and friends has improved 10 fold.  I also found that EQ burnout when doing this is almost non-existant.<br>
<br>
Just thought I would share this with you, since it has improved my life/lifestyle so much.<br>
<br>
Sekoryn - 60 Warlord<br>
