I know for me EQ has saved me thousands of dollars since I started playing it. <br>
Pre EQ: I would go out to clubs, spend tons on drinks and other recreational activities, taking dates out to nice dinners and getaways, pretty much always eating out cuz face it being single is boring when all alone in your apt. It all adds up to a lot from gasoline for the car to plane tickets and hotel rooms. $$$$$<br>
<br>
Present: I play EQ almost every night, cook dinner at home, go to family members house for dinner usually once every weekend, small things like a movie every now and again, skiing, sports events and concerts every once and a while. 2+ years of playing EQ got my finances in order enough to buy an Audi A4 Quatro cash and save up a substantial amount of money to put down on a house. <br>
Granted I'm still single and don't have the social life i once had, the day will come when EQ bores me enough to quit and I won't regret playing it for hours a day and the friends i have made in the game. And at that time i'll have a house to come home to that's all mine, a decent car that's all payed for, and friends and family that i have always had. Social life can wait for now, i'm having my kicks while i can...and when i get back into the dating scene it'll be nice to not have to bring dates home to some one bedroom apt and be more stable then I was. <br>
Looking back 2 years ago, I was living almost paycheck to paycheck, spending crazy amounts of money on nuggs(heh i have smoked no more than 5 times in 2 years where it was once easily 5 times in 1 day), making late payments on all my bills, and not being able to save more than $200 in any given month. Now I almost debt free(still have those damn student loans grrrr) Have 401k, Mutual fund, health insurance, a *gasp* retirement plan, been promoted twice at work and quit smoking cigarettes. <br>
I'll be 29 in April and I can't be happier with where my life is headed now than from where it was going before EQ which was nowhere. <br>
